    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_12688_f1000research_7563_1__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's research question is narrowly focused on tximport's ability to import Salmon files and produce three specific matrix types. The paper's scope is broader\u2014it compares gene-level vs. transcript-level analysis strategies across multiple quantification tools (Salmon, featureCounts, RSEM, kallisto, etc.) and statistical methods (edgeR, DESeq2, limma).",
        "The card emphasizes 'pre-constructed tx2gene mapping' as a requirement, but the paper does not explicitly discuss tx2gene table construction or Gencode v27 in the provided passages. The paper focuses on the conceptual and statistical advantages of gene-level analysis, not on the mechanics of building tx2gene tables.",
        "The card's title mentions 'Reproduce tx2gene table construction from Gencode v27' which is not addressed in the paper passages. The paper does not provide guidance on constructing tx2gene mappings from genome annotations."
      ],
