    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-usage-bias-correction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Accounting for the potentially varying average transcript length across samples when performing DGE, either in the definition of the count matrix (scaledTPM) or by defining offsets, led to considerably improved false discovery rate (FDR) control compared to using the observed feature Counts or aggregated Salmon counts (simplesum) directly",
      "asbval:note": "Core claim is directly supported. Paper demonstrates that sample-specific transcript length offsets improve DGE inference when differential isoform usage is present.",
