      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-usage-bias-correction/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We defined three different count matrices for each data set: 1) using feature Counts from the Rsubread R package (denoted feature Counts below), 2) summing the estimated transcript counts from Salmon within genes (simplesum), 3) summing the estimated transcript TPMs from Salmon within genes, and multiplying with the total library size in millions (scaledTPM)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly demonstrates aggregation of transcript-level counts to gene level.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "isoform-usage-bias-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You are aggregating transcript-level counts to gene level.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:13:39.301275+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-usage-bias-correction/012",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To facilitate a broad range of analysis choices, depending on the biological question of interest, we provide an R package, tximport, to import transcript lengths and abundance estimates from several popular quantification packages and export (estimated) count matrices and, optionally, average transcript length correction terms (i.e., offsets) that can be used as inputs to common statistical engines, such as DESeq2, edgeR and limma",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly names these three tools as compatible downstream engines.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "isoform-usage-bias-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Your downstream tool is DESeq2, edgeR, or limma-voom.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:13:39.301275+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-usage-bias-correction/013",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "It is important to note that this improvement is entirely attributable to an improved handling of genes with changes in isoform composition between the conditions... offsets must account for the differences in transcript usage between the samples and thus using (sample-independent) exon-union gene lengths will not improve performance",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates that sample-specific transcript length offsets are necessary to correct for differential isoform usage effects on gene-level fold changes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "isoform-usage-bias-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "The offset correction is essential because differential isoform usage changes the average transcript length per gene in a sample-specific manner, which would otherwise inflate or deflate gene-level fold-change estimates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:13:39.301275+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matrix-equivalence-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper does not discuss or validate equivalence between two alternative pathways (txOut=TRUE then summarizeToGene vs. txOut=FALSE). The paper focuses on comparing different quantification methods (Salmon, feature Counts, simplesum, scaledTPM) and their downstream statistical performance, not on validating computational equivalence between two tximport workflows.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
