    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Several different quantification approaches have been proposed... ranging from simple counting of reads that overlap given genomic regions to more complex estimation of underlying transcript abundances... we provide an R package, tximport, to import transcript lengths and abundance estimates from several popular quantification packages and export (estimated) count matrices... that can be used as inputs to common statistical engines, such as DESeq2, edgeR and limma",
      "asbval:note": "Scope description aligns with paper's stated purpose and use cases.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have transcript-level abundance estimates and inferred counts from salmon/kallisto/Sailfish (with or without Gibbs/bootstrap replicates) that must be summarized to gene or transcript level, and you plan to use count-based differential expression tools (e",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:15:23.533465+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The use of gene counts as input to statistical tools typically assumes that the length of the expressed part of a gene does not change across samples and thus length can therefore be ignored for differential analysis... Accounting for the potentially varying average transcript length across samples when performing DGE, either in the definition of the count matrix (scaledTPM) or by defining offsets, led to considerably improved false discovery rate (FDR) control",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly discusses the constant-length assumption and why sample-specific length offsets are needed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Normalization is mandatory when gene length varies across samples due to differential isoform usage, which violates the constant-length assumption of standard count-based models.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:15:23.533465+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-count-normalization/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "tximport, to import transcript lengths and abundance estimates from several popular quantification packages... Several software packages have been developed for performing such \"simple\" counting (e.g., feature Counts and HTSeq-count). More recently, the field has seen a surge in methods aimed at quantifying the abundances of individual transcripts (e.g., Cufflinks, RSEM, Bit Seq, kallisto and Salmon).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper distinguishes between simple counting tools (featureCounts, HTSeq) and transcript quantification tools (Salmon, kallisto, RSEM) that tximport is designed for.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-12688-f1000research-7563-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-count-normalization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
