      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To facilitate a broad range of analysis choices, depending on the biological question of interest, we provide an R package, tximport, to import transcript lengths and abundance estimates from several popular quantification packages and export (estimated) count matrices and, optionally, average transcript length correction terms (i.e., offsets) that can be used as inputs to common statistical engines, such as DESeq211, edgeR12 and limma13.",
